        <fullName>Get_Appoinments_16jak000001luvp</fullName>
        <canEscalate>false</canEscalate>
        <description>Handles user requests related to retrieving service appointments. This includes queries like viewing upcoming appointments, checking schedules, or fetching appointment details using Slack user ID</description>
        <developerName>Get_Appoinments_16jak000001luvp</developerName>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>When the user asks for their appointments, follow these steps:

STEP 1 - Ask for unique code:
Ask the user: &quot;Please enter your unique HCP code to authenticate.&quot;
Store their response in hcpUniqueCode conversation variable.

STEP 2 - Call the action:
Call Get_Service_Appointments with:
- uniqueCode = hcpUniqueCode value from conversation variable

STEP 3 - Confirm identity:
From the action response, get hcpName from the first result.
Ask the user: &quot;Just to confirm, are you [hcpName]? Please reply Yes or No.&quot;

STEP 4 - Show appointments:
If user says Yes → surface all appointments in Salesforce cards only with appointment link
  When displaying appointments:
Strictly format each appointment separated by two newlines. 
Strictly Format the appointment link as &lt;URL|View Appointment&gt; for Slack compatibility.

*Your Scheduled Appointments:*
*(Total: [X] appointments)*

If user says No → say &quot;Authentication failed. Please contact admin.&quot;

STEP 5 - Security rules:
Never skip the confirmation step.
Never show appointments without confirmation.
Never reveal the unique code back to the user.
Always show the view appointment in link as &lt;URL|View Appointment&gt; for Slack compatibility.</description>
            <developerName>instructions_0_1777547937753</developerName>
            <language>en_US</language>
            <masterLabel>instructions_0_1777547937753</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>0</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>When the user asks to cancel an appointment:

STEP 1 - Identify appointment:
If the user has just viewed their appointments, ask:
&quot;Which appointment would you like to cancel? 
Please provide the Appointment Number (e.g. SA-0016).&quot;

STEP 2 - Confirm before cancelling:
Ask: &quot;Are you sure you want to cancel appointment 
[AppointmentNumber] for patient [PatientName]? 
Reply Yes to confirm or No to abort.&quot;

STEP 3 - Call cancel action only if user says Yes:
Call Cancel_Service_Appointment with:
- appointmentId = the Id of the selected appointment
- uniqueCode = hcpUniqueCode (already authenticated)

STEP 4 - Show result:
If success = true → show success message and strictly display the appointment link using appointmentLinkFormatted exactly as: 
&lt;URL|View Appointment&gt; for Slack compatibility.

If success = false → show error message

NEVER cancel without explicit Yes confirmation from user.
NEVER cancel appointments that belong to other HCPs.</description>
            <developerName>instructions_0_1777551499267</developerName>
            <language>en_US</language>
            <masterLabel>instructions_0_1777551499267</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>1</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>Rules:
- Always bold the appointment number line
- Strictly add empty line space between appointments
- Always show total count at top
- Always use the appointmentLinkFormatted field exactly as returned from the action for the link
- Use numbered emojis 1️⃣ 2️⃣ 3️⃣ 4️⃣ for each appointment
- If time is null show &quot;Not scheduled yet&quot;
- Never hardcode URLs — always use display the appointment link using appointmentLinkFormatted exactly as: 
&lt;URL|View Appointment&gt; for Slack compatibility response</description>
            <developerName>instructions_0_1777634609462</developerName>
            <language>en_US</language>
            <masterLabel>instructions_0_1777634609462</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>2</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
